OL,3,CWoman first ever to give British Sign
OL,4,CLanguage speech at Buckingham Palace
OL,6,FA young deaf woman from Aberystwyth,
OL,7,FCeredigion, has become the first
OL,8,Fperson to give a speech in British
OL,9,FSign Language (BSL) at Buckingham
OL,10,FPalace.
OL,12,FHafwen Clarke, 19, made history in
OL,13,Ffront of about 2,000 people as she
OL,14,Freceived her gold Duke of Edinburgh
OL,15,FAward.
OL,17,FMs Clarke, who teaches others BSL as a
OL,18,Fyouth helper at St John Ambulance,
OL,19,Ftold the reception: "I'm very proud to
OL,20,Fbe here so I can show the world what
OL,21,Fdeaf people can do.
